node.text: The living legend @MikeHornExplorer tells us about the horrible scenes he has witnessed during his adventures and the importance of the young generations in the race to save our planet ! We must all get together now and start moving, it’s time for action ! Our special thanks to @spgrytz for supporting our vision towards a sustainable environment! #DiscoverEarth

node.text:
Mentally wondering around the gorgeous streets of Italy ☀️🇮🇹 Do you have a favourite Italian city or town?

Trulli di Alberobello, located in the southern region of Puglia, is a magical World Heritage Site known for its narrow streets, traditional architecture and storybook-like features. Would you visit this beautiful commune?

📍 Alberobello, Italy

🇮🇹 #discoverItaly with @micheizzo

Uncovering one of the 7 New Wonders of the World with @visualsofjulius 🤯

Located in Jordan, Petra (also known as “Rose City), is a famous archaeological site with a heritage that goes all the way back to 300 B.C.. Petra’s pink and red sandstone cliffs are home to stunning, ornate tombs and temples, making it an unforgettable site for tourists. Would you visit Petra?

📍Jordan

🇯🇴 #discoverJordan with @visualsofjulius

node.text:
Quiet mornings in the best company 🦌✨ Would you join these white deer for a walk in the forest?

While some deer are now extinct in Bangladesh and Pakistan, you can still come across them in regions of central and Northern India, and in Nepal. They’re also called the Barasingha (meaning twelve ends), which refers to the many-tined antlers of these majestic deer.

📍Himachal Pradesh, india

🇮🇳#discoverIndia via @discoverwildlife

node.text:
Tranquil autumn shades in Vermont 🍂✨ What is your favourite season?

Autumn brings a coat of orange, red and yellow to Vermont’s farms, villages and mountains, making the landscape even more dreamy. 

Insider tip: If you’re headed to Vermont (especially during this season), you should definitely hike up Mount Mansfield to enjoy the views from the top ⛰️ 

 📍Vermont, United States

node.text:
Climbing the Visapur Fort’s Waterfall Stairway 💦 Would you take on this hike?

India’s Visapur Fort is one of the highest hill forts of the area. Luckily, the Visapur Trek has a moderate difficulty level, which means that with the right equipment, it’s suitable even for beginners. 

Insider tip: If you’d like to trek through a waterfall for a big part of the trail (as well as see the area’s green surroundings truly come to life), you could plan your visit during monsoon season. 🍃

📍Visapur Fort, India

🇮🇳 #discoverIndia with @swapneil_7
